This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for extracting medical events and their attributes from unstructured text in Electronic Health Record (EHR) notes. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. 

The paper also explores various recurrent neural network frameworks, which are a popular machine learning technique for NLP tasks. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. 

Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which covers a broad range of topics related to AI and machine learning, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with techniques for searching and analyzing large collections of text data, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which covers topics related to neural networks and other machine learning techniques.
